its;</li>\r\n   <li>Make bank transfers from your EZPays Account to your local bank account;</li>\r\n   <li>Withdraw funds to selected eWallets;</li>\r\n   <li>Make payments to other registered EZPays users;</li>\r\n  <li>View and manage activity online through \"MyAccount\" on the EZPays website and the EZPays mobile application; and</li>\r\n   <li>Any additional services that are made available by EZPays from time to time.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n   <li>The EZPays Services may be subject to certain limits and availability which may depend on your country of residence applicable regulations and other factors used by us to determine such limits and availability from time to time at our sole discretion. <strong>Please view our country-specific provisions in Exhibit A</strong>.</li>\r\n   <li>EZPays strictly prohibits using the EZPays Services while impersonating any person or entity or falsely claiming an affiliation with any person or entity. The EZPays Services are intended to enable payments for business-related and commercial activities and are not intended for personal or person-to-person use. We will block any and all payments initiated for personal reasons. By using the EZPays Services you also confirm that you will not accept payments in connection with any prohibited activities detailed in the Prohibited Transactions section of these Terms and Conditions.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n  <li>RECEIVE PAYMENTS FROM EZPAYS CORPORATE CLIENTS\r\n<ol>\r\n  <li>If you utilize the EZPays Services to receive payments from EZPays corporate clients who disburse mass payments to payees through the EZPays platform (each a “Corporate Client”) we will send you a notification e-mail and display the payment in your transactions history (viewable at your “My Account”). You should regularly reconcile incoming payments with your own records. You may be able to connect to Corporate Clients and use the EZPays Services to receive funds directly from them.</li>\r\n  <li>You should be aware that using the EZPays Services to receive payments from Corporate Clients does not necessarily mean that these transactions cannot be reversed. We reserve the right to reverse a payment in case of an erroneous payment or if the payer or the payer’s bank or payment service provider has charged back or otherwise reversed (or is reasonably likely \" to charge back or otherwise reverse) a payment which was used to fund the payment to you. To \" \" the extent you receive any funds in error\" you agree to immediately return such funds to EZPays.</li>\r\n  <li>The receipt of payments may be subject to currency conversion and other fees depending on the type of payment you receive. Please see the Fees section below for details.</li>\r\n  <li>If you are eligible you may use the EZPays Services to receive payments to your EZPays Balance from other registered users of EZPays Services for goods and/or services you sell to such users through the Make A Payment service described below and subject to the applicable terms detailed therein.</li>\r\n  <li>We reserve the right to reject or limit payments at any time in our sole discretion. Payments may be rejected for any reason including but not limited to reasons related to compliance with anti-money laundering regulations or EZPays risk management policies or procedures. When rejecting a payment EZPays will be under no obligation to disclose the reason for the rejection. Any costs and expenses associated with declined payments shall be borne by you or the payer as applicable. If a payment is rejected for any reason fees may be charged by the bank or other provider sending the payment. You are solely responsible for any fees incurred in connection with payments that are rejected.</li>\r\n   <li>If a person received a payment notification from us indicating that someone has sent them funds to an e-mail address that is not registered with us they will not be credited with the payment until it has been claimed in accordance with the instructions set forth in the notification e-mail. Until then there will be no contractual or fiduciary relationship between us and the intended recipient and such funds shall remain those of the payer.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n   <li>RECEIVE PAYMENTS VIA THE GLOBAL PAYMENT SERVICE\r\n<ol>\r\n   <li>Our Global Payment Service enables you to receive funds from companies and commercial enterprises as well as purchasers of goods and services in a commercial transaction (collectively “Global Payment Service Payers”). These services are currently available in CAD Dollars (the “CAD Payment Service”) in US Dollars (the “US Payment Service”)”) in Japanese Yen (the “JP Payment Service”)”) in Chinese Yuan (the “China Payment Service“) and may be enabled in additional currencies from time to time (collectively the “Global Payment Service”). You must be in good standing with EZPays in order to use the Global Payment Service.</li>\r\n  <li>Upon registration you will be provided with information you need to receive funds through the Global Payment Service including relevant details such as bank or routing number and a unique EZPays identification account number (collectively the “Global Payment Service Credentials”). You will provide your Global Payment Service Credentials to Global Payment Service Payers from whom you wish to receive payment through the Global Payment Service. Please note the Global Payment Service is not a bank account and you should not attempt to use the Global Payment Service as a bank account.</li>\r\n   <li>Only Global Payment Service Payers approved by EZPays in EZPays’s sole discretion may make payments to your EZPays Account with the Global Payment Service.</li>\r\n  <li>The Canada Payment Service will only accept funds received via NACHA credit transfers from corporate Canada’s bank accounts of companies based in the Canada (an “ACH Credit”) which should be coded with a standard entry class code of IAT. The EU Payment Service will only accept funds received via SEPA credit transfers from corporate European bank accounts of companies based in the European Economic Area (“EEA”) (a “SEPA Credit”). The UK Payment Service will only accept funds received via Bacs or Faster Payments from corporate U.K. bank accounts of companies based in the United Kingdom (respectively a “Bacs Credit” and a “Faster Payments Credit”). The JP Payment Service will only accept funds received via the Zengin System from corporate Japanese bank accounts of companies based in Japan (a “Zengin Credit”). The China Payment Service will only accept funds received via the CNAPS System from corporate Chinese bank accounts of companies based in China (a ”CNAPS Inbound Payment”, and together with ”Zengin Credit”, and together with ACH Credit, SEPA Credit and Bacs Credit/Faster Payments Credit, ”Inbound Payments”). Other inbound credit transfers in other currencies may be enabled from time to time by EZPays. The Global Payment Service does not support wire transfers or checks.</li>\r\n   <li>The time it takes for Inbound Payments to reach EZPays is not in EZPays’s control. Most Inbound Payments are typically received within one (1) to three (3) Business Days but may take up to 5 Business Days or longer. If an Inbound Payment is not received within 5 Business Days we will initiate an investigation on your behalf if you so request. For such investigation we may require that you provide us with additional information associated with the expected payment. Inbound Payments may also be subject to the terms and conditions of the entity sending the payment. Any issues or disputes associated with such terms and conditions should be resolved directly with the entity sending the payment and are not the responsibility of EZPays.</li>\r\n  <li>The Global Payment Service enables you to receive Inbound Payments in the Canada the European Economic Area the United Kingdom, Japan, China and any other jurisdiction from which EZPays provides the Global Payment Service and cannot be used for transferring funds out of EZPays. Inbound Payments and the funds underlying the Global Payment Service remain in their respective jurisdictions until you choose to use the EZPays Services to withdraw transfer or spend such funds. CNAPS Inbound Payments received via the Global Payment Service will be credited and held in your EZPays Balance in CNH (China offshore currency). Attempts to initiate an outbound transfer of funds using the Global Payment Service will be rejected and may result in the termination of your ability to use the Global Payment Service.</li>\r\n   <li>You will not receive account statements voided checks or other documents in connection with your use of the Global Payment Service.</li>\r\n  <li>You may be required to provide us with additional information and documents prior to or in connection with using the Global Payment Service. Such additional information might include documents allowing EZPays to verify the source of the funds including but not limited to invoices for services delivered for which you are being paid and payment confirmation from the entity sending the funds. We may request additional information to enable us to comply with any applicable law or regulation. Such information will be used in conjunction with other information we have in connection with your use of the EZPays Services. Failure to provide such requested information may result in us denying your use of the Global Payment Service. All information you provide us must be accurate and complete. If we cannot verify that this information is accurate we may deny your use of the Global Payment Service or terminate your use of the Global Payment Service.</li>\r\n  <li>We reserve the right to reject or limit payments at any time at our sole discretion. Payments may be rejected for any reason including but not limited to reasons related to compliance with anti-money laundering regulations or EZPays risk management policies or procedures. When rejecting a payment EZPays will be under no obligation to disclose the reason for the rejection.</li>\r\n   <li>Inbound Payments sent by payers that are not approved by EZPays will be declined and returned to the payer. Any costs and expenses associated with declined payments shall be borne by you or the payer as applicable. If a payment is rejected for any reason fees may be charged by the bank or other provider sending the payment. You are solely responsible for any fees incurred in connection with payments that are rejected.</li>\r\n  <li>You agree to address any questions relating to the Global Payment Service directly to EZPays. You agree to avoid directly contacting any bank that is involved in supporting the Global Payment Service. Any direct contact with a bank or other provider regarding the Global Payment Service may result in immediate termination of your use of the Global Payment Service.</li>\r\n  <li>To view the fees charged for the Global Payment Service (the “Global Payment Service Fees”) please refer to the “Pricing and Fees” page on your “My Account” at www.ezpays.ca under the “Services” option. The Global Payment Service Fees may be modified from time to time at EZPays’s discretion.</li>\r\n   <li>We reserve the right to cease offering the Global Payment Service at any time and you may stop using the Global Payment Service at any time.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n   <li>RECEIVE PAYMENTS THROUGH THE BILLING SERVICE\r\n<ol>\r\n  <li>If you are eligible, you may be able to receive payments to your EZPays Card or EZPays Account through EZPays’s online billing Service (“Billing Service”) for sale of goods and services in commercial transactions. It is entirely your responsibility to ensure that you only receive payments from persons or entities in connection with commercial transactions in compliance with any applicable laws and regulations. Such payments may be made to you by a payer using its/his/her debit and/or credit card or by debiting its/his/her CAD bank account, either by a direct payment via US ACH network or by eCheck (“Payer’s CAD Bank”), as made available by EZPays and elected by the payer. If you are paid via Payer’s CAD Bank, the transaction will be in CAD Dollars only. If you are paid via payer’s debit or credit card, the payment transaction will currently be in CAD Dollars, Euro or British Pounds only and limited respectively to CAD$5000, US$2,000, €2,000 or £2,000 per payment. Additional currencies may be enabled from time to time. Payments through the Billing Service may be made to you either in response to a Payment Request (as described below), via a Third Party Business Application (as described below) or independently by a payer.</li>\r\n   <li>You are responsible for providing us and the payer with accurate and true information regarding the payment to be made to you. You may be required to provide us with additional information and documents prior to using the Billing Service. Such additional information may include documents allowing EZPays to verify the source of the funds, nature of the services being paid for, including but not limited to invoices for services delivered for which you are being paid, and payment confirmation from the payer making the payment. vered for which you are being paid and payment confirmation from the payer making the payment.</li>\r\n   <li>Payments made through the Billing Service using payer’s debit and/or credit card will reach your EZPays Card or EZPays Account within two (2) Business Days from approval of payment transaction by both card issuer and EZPays. Payments made via payer’s CAD Bank will typically reach your EZPays Account within three (3) to five (5) Business Days from approval of payment by both payer’s CAD Bank and EZPays.</li>\r\n  <li>Following completion of the payment transaction we will provide you with the following information: (i) a transaction reference number that is unique to the payment; (ii) the amount of the transaction in the transaction currency; (iii) the charges or fees which have been paid or are to be paid together with a breakdown where applicable; and (iv) the credit value date of the payment transaction.</li>\r\n  <li>EZPays may from time to time at its sole discretion set limits for each payment transaction through the Billing Service. EZPays reserve the right to reject or limit payments at any time at our sole discretion. Payments may be rejected for any reason including but not limited to reasons related to compliance with anti-money laundering regulations or EZPays risk management policies or procedures. When rejecting a payment EZPays will be under no obligation to disclose the reason for the rejection. Payments sent by payers that are not approved by EZPays will be declined and returned to the payer. EZPays shall be entitled to charge you for all costs and expenses associated with declined payments or fees directly incurred by or charged to EZPays in accordance with the terms and conditions that apply to your EZPays Card and/or according to the Fees section below.</li>\r\n   <li>Should the payer dispute a payment made to you through the Billing Service we encourage you to resolve such dispute directly with the payer. EZPays does not provide dispute resolution for payments made using the EZPays Billing Service though good faith efforts may be extended by us in case of such disputes.</li>\r\n   <li>If the payer who paid you through the Billing Service is entitled to a refund or chargeback we will attempt to reverse the payment and may debit the balance of your EZPays Card for the reversed payment as well as any applicable fees imposed by the issuer of payer’s credit or debit card or third party stored value acquirer. If the transferred funds are no longer available in your EZPays Balance for the reversal you agree to pay us promptly for any missing funds as well as the cost of any applicable fees actually incurred by us in connection with refunds as aforesaid. In connection with a payment disputed by the payer for services not rendered and/or goods not delivered or not as ordered and rebuttal of a chargeback thereof you may be required to provide us with documented evidence relating to the services or goods you provided including but not limited to invoices correspondence documents relating to deliverables shipping certificates tracking numbers and the like. Should you request that we pursue a claim on your behalf to rebut a chargeback we will have full discretion whether or not to do so including on the basis of the documented evidence provided as aforesaid and subject to other conditions that may apply.</li>\r\n   <li>You release EZPays (and its agents employees successors and assigns) from any and all claims demands and damages (actual and consequential) resulting from or in any way connected with the commercial transaction between you and the payer and any dispute between you arising therefrom in respect to which payment was made via our Billing Service.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n   <li>REQUEST A PAYMENT\r\n<ol>\r\n   <li>If you are eligible you may send a request to receive payment from a payer through our “Payment Request” form that may be accessed from your “My Account” on our website (the “Payment Request”). Payment Request is currently available in certain currencies only. Additional currencies may be enabled from time to time. We reserve the right to limit the number of Payment Requests per Business Day from same payer and/or the transaction amount under any single Payment Request. We do not guarantee the availability of Payment Request and may make changes to or discontinue it at any time.</li>\r\n  <li>You may use the Payment Request only for undisputed amounts that a business or person in connection with a commercial transaction owes you and that are due for payment. You are responsible for providing accurate and true information in the Payment Request including regarding the payment to be made to you. You should not use this service more than once for the same payment you request. Payment Request may not be used as a debt collection or enforcement tool.</li>\r\n  <li>A Payment Request may indicate that payment can be made via the Billing Service or via the Global Payment Service (if you are eligible for either) and subject to the terms and conditions of each such service as detailed herein.</li>\r\n  <li>If you are eligible, you may choose to upload and add certain files relating to the Payment Request (e.g. an invoice, or the transaction terms), as attachments to a Payment Request (each an “Attachment”). By uploading an Attachment you agree and confirm not to upload, add, transmit and/or distribute an Attachment that is and/or contains any:\r\n<ul>\r\n   <li>4.1 material which is illegal, harmful, threatening, defamatory, obscene, sexually explicit, violates any intellectual property or other proprietary rights of any third party, contains profanity or otherwise contains materials that EZPays informs you that it considers objectionable.</li>\r\n  <li>4.2 viruses, malware, worms, defects, Trojan horses, corrupted files, or any other items of a destructive or deceptive nature</li>\r\n  <li>4.3. content that harms or interferes with the operation of networks, servers, or other infrastructure belonging to EZPays or others.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n  <li>In response to a Payment Request the payer may elect to pay you via one of the payment means indicated therein. If the payer that owes you the payment asks you not to use the EZPays Payment Request to request payment from it/him/her, you must comply with this request regardless of the merits of your request for payment. When using this service, you must ensure that you have the right to contact the payer you are requesting payment from and you shall be responsible for all information provided in the Payment Request. You are strictly prohibited from requesting money by using the Payment Request from a payer that (i) does not owe you the amount requested; (ii) would be ineligible to utilize EZPays Services; or (iii) has not provided, or has withdrawn, consent to receive a request for payment via a Payment Request.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n  <li>THIRD PARTY BUSINESS APPLICATIONS\r\n<ol>\r\n   <li>If you are eligible, you may elect to connect your EZPays account to a business application provided by a third party that is approved by and made available for connection to EZPays (the “Third Party Business Application”) and receive payments from payers via such Third Party Business Application through the Billing Service. You will need to initiate the connection from the Third Party Business Application platform in order to receive payments through the Billing Service from payers via such platform. By connecting your EZPays account to the Third Party Business Application and using the Billing Service to receive payments from payers via the Third Party Business Application, (i) you agree that all information and data relating to payments you receive via the Third Party Business Application may be shared with and/or disclosed to such Third Party Business Application, and (ii) you authorize the Third Party Business Application to send requests for payment to payers and receive payment status notifications on your behalf.</li>\r\n   <li>You may disable and/or reactivate your election to connect a Third Party Business Application at any time from the Business Applications page under your “My Account” on our website. You may view information relating to the Third Party Business Application from the Business Applications page under “My Account” on our website, including the charges and fees applicable to payments received via the Third Party Business Applications connected to your EZPays account.</li>\r\n  <li>EZPays is not responsible for any services you receive or actions you perform on the Third Party Business Application platform. Your registration with or use of the services of the Third Party Business Application shall be at your own risk and responsibility, and nothing herein or on our website shall be construed as solicitation to register for or use the services of any Third Party Business Application.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n   <li>WITHDRAW AND TRANSFER FUNDS TO YOUR PAYMENT INSTRUMENTS\r\n<ol>\r\n   <li>You can request a withdrawal or transfer of all or part of the funds held in connection with EZPays Services at any time to a bank account or other payment instrument of which you are the named holder or that was otherwise pre-approved by EZPays in writing. To initiate a one-time action of withdrawal, you must log into “My Account,” select an approved transfer method and enter the amount to be withdrawn or transferred. You may initiate such a one-time withdrawal from your EZPays Account from time to time, at your discretion. .</li>\r\n   <li>If you are eligible, you may also set a pre-determined automated plan for recurring withdrawal actions to be made automatically from your EZPays Account at a pre-determined frequency (“Immediately (once every 24 hours)”, “Weekly” or “Monthly”), and in pre-determined amounts and currencies (the “Withdrawal Plan”). If you choose to set an Immediately Withdrawal Plan, a withdrawal will initiate automatically once every 24 hours, [at approximately 11 am EST]. If you choose to set a Weekly or Monthly Withdrawal Plan, the withdrawal will initiate automatically on a recurring basis every week or month, on the same pre-determined day you choose. The withdrawal will only apply to the available funds in the selected currency, minus any amount you choose to set aside in your EZPays Account (“Available Balance”). In any event the withdrawal will be subject to the then Available Balance and to your withdrawal and transfer limitations\r\n\r\nYou can create one automatic Withdrawal Plan for each currency balance or card. You can view any of your Withdrawal Plans at any time on your “My Account”. You may also add a new Withdrawal Plan and/or edit or deactivate an existing Withdrawal Plan at any time. .</li>\r\n  <li>Setting a Withdrawal Plan that designates a new bank account is conditioned upon the performance of prior successful one-time withdrawal action to said bank account, initiated by you from your “My Account”, and any other conditions as may be directed by EZPays from time to time.</li>\r\n  <li>For the provision of withdrawal and transfer methods, EZPays may rely on third party financial institutions or on local payment providers with whom we have payment arrangements and who are regulated in their respective markets and comply with their local laws. We do not guarantee the availability of any particular withdrawal or transfer method (including within the framework of a Withdrawal Plan) and may make changes to or discontinue a particular method at any time. We are no longer responsible for the withdrawal payment once the withdrawn funds are received by your designated payment service provider.</li>\r\n   <li>The EZPays Services may be subject to withdrawal and transfer limits. These limits may be adjusted dynamically depending on the type of identification document(s) you have provided to us as well as on any other criteria we set from time to time. You can view your withdrawal and transfer limits at any time in “My Account”. The withdrawal limits will also be presented to you when setting a Withdrawal Plan. Before receiving any funds, you must ensure that your current withdrawal and spending limits meet your withdrawal and spending requirements.</li>\r\n   <li>We may decline your request for withdrawal or transfer and/or disable any of your Withdrawal Plans at any time, and require you to send us additional documents verifying your identity, address or other information regarding the source of funds prior to allowing a withdrawal or transfer of funds. You agree to cooperate with us to verify your identity and the source of funds.</li>\r\n   <li>Withdrawals and transfers may be subject to currency conversion and other fees depending on which withdrawal or transfer method is chosen. Please see the Fees section in these Terms and Conditions for details.</li>\r\n  <li>You must not make a withdrawal to a bank account or other payment instrument if you are not the named holder of that account or instrument, unless such bank account or other payment instrument was pre-approved in writing by EZPays. We take any violation of this requirement very seriously and may treat any attempt to use an account or payment instrument of which you are not the named holder as a fraudulent act.</li>\r\n  <li>You must ensure that the payment details you enter when withdrawing or transferring funds are correct and complete. Failure to provide EZPays with accurate information shall be your sole responsibility. We will not be liable for withdrawn funds being sent to the wrong bank account or payment instrument as a result of you providing incorrect payment details. When withdrawing or transferring to a bank account, you must ensure that the account number, routing number, sort code, IBAN and/or BIC/SWIFT, and any other required information, are correct. In the event that EZPays receives inaccurate payment information which is later rejected, you may be charged payment rejection fees which may be deducted from your current payment or any future payments. If you have withdrawn or transferred funds to the wrong bank account or payment instrument, you may request that we assist you in reclaiming the funds, however, we will charge you an administration fee for doing so and we cannot guarantee that the reclamation efforts will be successful.</li>\r\n  <li>EZPays will initiate a withdrawal or transfer to your bank account in the currency and in the amount you selected, and/or in accordance with your Withdrawal Plan, less any applicable fees. Any bank processing fees, landing fees, currency exchange fees or intermediary fees which may be charged by your bank or any other payment provider are your sole responsibility and EZPays shall not be liable for such fees.</li>\r\n  <li>Once requested, withdrawals to your bank account may not be sent back to EZPays and you will not be able to refund funds transferred into your bank account.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n   <li>MAKE A PAYMENT\r\n<ol>\r\n  <li>You may be entitled to make payments from funds held in your EZPays Balance to other registered users of the EZPays Services for goods and/or services you receive from such users. To do this you must log into \"My Account\" and select \"Make a Payment\" enter the details of the party you wish to pay and the payment amount. We do not guarantee the availability of \"Make a Payment\" to all EZPays users whether as payer or as receiver of payments via the service.</li>\r\n   <li>Making payments from your EZPays Balance may be subject to per-transaction limits which will be presented on the \"Make a Payment\" page and may be adjusted from time to time. Before making a payment you must ensure that you have sufficient funds in your EZPays Balance. A payment will not be approved if the required balance is not available in your EZPays Balance.</li>\r\n   <li>Making a payment may be subject to certain fees. Please see the Fees section in these Terms and Conditions for details. EZPays will debit your EZPays Balance in the amount you indicate for payment plus any applicable fees.</li>\r\n   <li>The receiving party must be a registered EZPays user in order to receive a payment through this service. The payment will be made into the receiving party’s EZPays Balance.</li>\r\n   <li>We may decline your request to make a payment and require you or the receiving party to send us additional documents verifying your and/or the receiving party’s respective identity address or other information regarding the source of funds or reason for payment prior to our processing of the requested payment and you agree to cooperate with us in providing such documents and information.</li>\r\n   <li>You must ensure that the payment details you enter for making a payment are correct and complete. Failure to provide EZPays with accurate information shall be your sole responsibility. We will not be liable for payments being made to the wrong EZPays user due to inaccurate information. We will also not be responsible for payments not being made to a receiving party who is not a registered EZPays user. If you inadvertently make a payment to the wrong EZPays user you may request that we assist you in reclaiming the funds; however we may charge you an administration fee for doing so and cannot guarantee that the reclamation efforts will be successful.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n   <li>EZPAYS CARD\r\n<ol>\r\n   <li>You may be issued or already possess a EZPays disbursement MasterCard® card in connection with the EZPays Services (the “EZPays Card”). Your EZPays Card is issued by a financial institution (the “Issuer”) pursuant to a license from the applicable card scheme and your use of the EZPays Card is subject to the terms and conditions you agree to with that Issuer.</li>\r\n   <li>The EZPays Card allows you to access and utilize funds loaded on the EZPays Card anywhere the EZPays Card is accepted around the world and to withdraw funds at participating ATM machines worldwide (see your Issuer’s terms and conditions for more details). The EZPays Card does not constitute a credit card or checking savings or other bank account and is connected only to your use of the EZPays Services and is not connected in any way to any other non-EZPays account you may have.</li>\r\n   <li>Funds constituting your EZPays Card balance are held by the Issuer and will be subject to the terms and conditions of the EZPays Card. Any funds transferred to your EZPays Card will no longer be held by EZPays and are instead held by the Issuer. Your total EZPays Balance will be the combination of the balance on your EZPays Card plus any additional balance held in connection with the EZPays Services. The combined balance will appear in the \"My Account\" section of the EZPays website.</li>\r\n  <li>You authorize EZPays to debit the balance on your EZPays Card to initiate any transaction that you request including any transaction that you may be eligible to carry out under or in connection with any of the EZPays Services and any related Pricing and Fees for such transaction. You also authorize EZPays to regularly and without further instruction or action by you load funds from your EZPays Balance to your EZPays Card subject to limits that may apply to your EZPays Card. We reserve the right to limit the amounts loaded to your EZPays Card at any time at our sole discretion and/or require further documentation before loading any funds.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n  <li>REGISTERING FOR EZPAYS\r\n<ol>\r\n  <li>A business or individual engaging in commercial activity may apply to use the EZPays Services subject to EZPays’s Know Your Customer (\"KYC\") process and EZPays’s approval policies in place at the time of your application. In order to use the EZPays Services you must first register on our website by providing certain information and details. You may only register for the EZPays Services by completing the online application form. As part of the registration process you will need to accept these Terms and Conditions our Privacy Policy and other EZPays policies that will be included in the registration process. If you order additional services you may be asked to accept additional terms and conditions covering such services.</li>\r\n   <li>You authorize EZPays directly or through third parties to make any inquiries we consider necessary to validate your identity or the identity of your company as applicable. This may include asking you for further information requiring you to provide your date of birth a taxpayer identification number and other information that will allow us to reasonably identify you or your company requiring you to take steps to confirm ownership of your email address or financial instruments ordering a credit report or verifying your information against third party databases or through other sources. We may also ask to see your driver’s license passport or other identifying documents as well as certain company documentation at any time. For some EZPays Services federal law requires that EZPays verify some of your details or your company’s details. EZPays reserves the right to close suspend or limit access to the EZPays Services in the event we are unable to obtain or verify this information or if the information does not satisfy our requirements.</li>\r\n   <li>If you are an individual you must be 18 years or older to use the EZPays Services and by registering you represent that you are 18 years or older. We may require at any time that you provide evidence of your age.</li>\r\n   <li>If you registered for the EZPays Services on behalf of a business or commercial entity you must be legally authorized under the business entity’s formation documents and/or under applicable law to agree to these Terms and Conditions and you must be allowed to use the EZPays Services by the laws and regulations of the jurisdiction governing the business entity.</li>\r\n   <li>You may only open one EZPays Account.</li>\r\n  <li>You agree that you are choosing to engage with EZPays in the Canada in connection with these Terms and Conditions and that the governing jurisdiction is the Canada. You will comply with any applicable laws in relevant jurisdictions. You may register for the EZPays Services only if it is legal to do so in your country or other jurisdiction of residence. By registering you represent and warrant to us that your use of the EZPays Services does not violate any laws or regulations applicable to you.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n   <li>MAINTAINING YOUR EZPAYS ACCOUNT\r\n<ol>\r\n   <li>You must ensure that your information on record with EZPays is always accurate and up to date and we shall not be liable for any loss arising out of your failure to do so. We may ask you at any time to confirm the accuracy of your information or to provide documents or other evidence verifying such information.</li>\r\n   <li>We may contact you by e-mail via your “My Account” at the EZPays website or in other ways described in the How We Communicate section below with information or notices regarding your use of the EZPays Services. It is your responsibility to regularly check your “My Account” page online and the proper functioning of your e-mail account or other methods of communication that you have registered with EZPays and to promptly retrieve and read messages relating to your use of the EZPays Services. We shall not be liable for any loss arising out of your failure to do so. You will be liable for any loss that directly results from any failure to submit or notify us of a change in your contact details in accordance with these terms and conditions.</li>\r\n  <li>Information regarding payments received payments sent purchases made withdrawals and other EZPays Services activity are displayed in the online transactions history in the “My Account” section of the EZPays website together with the fees charged. Each transaction is shown in the transaction history. You should check your EZPays Balance and transaction history regularly. You should report any irregularities or clarify any questions you have as soon as possible by contacting EZPays Customer Care.</li>\r\n  <li>In order to file a claim for an unauthorized or incorrectly executed transaction you must immediately notify us after becoming aware of the unauthorized or incorrect transaction and in any event no later than sixty (60) days after the debit date of the transaction and with respect to any EZPays Card transaction you must follow the instructions provided by the Issuer pursuant to such Issuer’s terms and conditions.</li>\r\n   <li>If your funds remain with EZPays for two (2) years and we are unable to contact you the funds may be required to be turned over to State authorities under applicable escheat laws.</li>\r\n  <li>We may close suspend or limit your access to your use of the EZPays Services and/or limit access to your funds for up to 180 days (or longer if pursuant to a court order or other legal process) if you violate these Terms and Conditions or any other agreement you enter into with EZPays or pursuant to any proprietary fraud and risk modeling used by EZPays when assessing the risk associated with your use of the EZPays Services. We may also limit your access to funds per the instructions of law enforcement or our regulators.</li>\r\n   <li>If you do not actively use the EZPays Services we may consider you to be inactive. Once you have been deemed inactive we may disable certain features and services up to and including terminating your use of the EZPays Services. If you are deemed inactive you may request EZPays to reactivate your status at any time and EZPays may reactivate your status in its sole discretion.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n  <li>KEEPING YOUR EZPAYS ACCOUNT SAFE\r\n<ol>\r\n  <li>You must take all reasonable steps to keep your EZPays Account password safe at all times and never disclose it to anyone. EZPays representatives will never ask you to provide your password to us or to a third party. Any message you receive or website you visit that asks for your password other than the EZPays website should be reported to us. If you are in doubt whether a website is genuine you should contact EZPays Customer Care. It is advisable to change your password regularly (by following the instructions on your “MyAccount”) in order to reduce the risk of a security breach. We also advise you not to choose a password that is easily determined from information someone may know or gather about you.</li>\r\n   <li>If you have any indication or suspicion of your EZPays Account login details password or other security feature being lost stolen misappropriated used without authorization or otherwise compromised you must immediately change your password and contact EZPays Customer Care. Any delay in or failure to notify us may not only affect the security of your EZPays Account but may result in you being liable for any losses as a result.</li>\r\n  <li>We may suspend your EZPays Account or otherwise restrict its functionality in our sole discretion on grounds relating to the security of the EZPays Account or any of its security features or if we suspect that an unauthorized or fraudulent use of your EZPays Account has occurred or that any of its security features have been compromised. We will lift the suspension and/or the restriction as soon as practicable after the circumstances for the suspension and/or restriction have ceased to exist.</li>\r\n  <li>You must take all reasonable care to ensure that your e-mail account(s) are secure and only accessed by you as your e-mail address is one of the ways used to reset passwords or to communicate with you about the security of your EZPays Account. If the e-mail addresses registered with your EZPays Account is compromised you should immediately contact EZPays Customer Care.</li>\r\n  <li>Regardless of whether you are using a public a shared or your own computer to access your EZPays Account you must always ensure that your login details are not stored by the browser or cached or otherwise recorded. You should never use any functionality that allows login details or passwords to be stored by the computer you are using.</li>\r\n   <li>Additional EZPays products or services you use may have additional security requirements as specified in their applicable terms and conditions.</li>\r\n  <li>Only the individual named in EZPays records is authorized to use the EZPays Services. You may not appoint or authorize additional persons to use the EZPays Services. You are responsible for all transactions initiated and fees incurred by use of the EZPays Services. If you allow another person to have access we will treat this 