ever you may be required to confirm your identity beforehand. There may be a minimum withdrawal or transfer amount as well as threshold limits as may be modified and disclosed from time to time. Sufficient funds must be available to cover any applicable fees. You can choose from the approved methods of withdrawal when submitting your withdrawal request.</li>\r\n  <li>The EZPays Services are not a bank account nor do they offer the features and benefits of a traditional bank account. The funds held in connection with the EZPays Services do not earn any interest. The funds are held by EZPays for your future use of EZPays Services. By accepting these Terms and Conditions you acknowledge that FDIC or other government-sponsored insurance does not apply to funds held in connection with the EZPays Services. In the unlikely event that we become insolvent you may lose the stored value held in connection with the EZPays Services. However we strictly adhere to applicable requirements which are designed to ensure the safety and liquidity of funds held on behalf of customers including segregation of customer funds and having secured surety bonds to provide additional security for your funds.</li>\r\n  <li>The funds held by EZPays belong to the person or legal entity that registered for the EZPays Services. No person or entity other than such registered user has any rights in relation to the funds held in connection with the EZPays Services. You may not assign or transfer your right to utilize the EZPays Services to a third party or otherwise grant any third party a legal or equitable interest in connection with your use of the EZPays Services.</li>\r\n   <li>The EZPays Services may include some or all of the following services which may change from time to time:\r\n<ul>\r\n   <li>Receive payments from EZPays corporate mass payout clients;</li>\r\n  <li>Receive payments from companies and commercial enterprises via our Global Payment Services;</li>\r\n  <li>Receive payments from 